\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 CHOREOGRAPHIC THEATRE\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Under Lili\'d5s Balcony Theatre Company }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 was created in 1995 in Wellington, New Zealand. Stephen Bain (NZ) and France Herv\'8e (France) are co-authors and directors of 6 plays in the repertoire of the company.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 The company opened classes of }
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 Choreographic Theatre}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  in a number of schools of Theatre and Dance, both in France and New Zealand, and frequently participate in performances outside the context of traditional theatre.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2The theatre is where we live out what we cannot in daily life, where we discover our full potential, our essence, and where we express a lifetime of experiences in the space of a moment.\'d3 Stephen Bain}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Research\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Under Lili\'d5s Balcony Theatre Co.}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  initiates programmes of theatrical research within independant structures in order to follow the exploration and development of theatre-making. They are receptive to other companies also wishing to pursue this area of investigation.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 (Residency programme at FACTORY, Department of English, Theatre and Film, VUW\: A study of cinematic techniques apted to a theatrical context - published in Winter \'d499 issue of International Performance Research.)\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Stephen Bain and France Herv\'8e work in constant dialogue with composers, architect-designers, filmakers and visual artists. The cross-polination of artistic disciplines reveals their collective vision to integrate key creative elements (image, projection, s}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 oundscape). \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2The stage should be a truely DYNAMIC space, rich in texture and colour, never in a state of permanence. Inevitably, it is in this state of uncertainty, that we (the audience) become deeply implicated in the compositional form, the quality of light, or the}
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1  pure movement through space.\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 STYLE \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 The}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  style of }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Under Lili\'d5s Balcony Theatre}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Co. is born from the fusion of a text-based direction, aiming at a natural interpretation,  and a choreo-}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 graphic }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  direction involving the movement (actors, lights, architecture) as vectors of unexpected metaphor.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Dramaturgy\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Onirisme\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Dynamic\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Concordance}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2The aesthetic of each production aims to challenge the imagination of the audience, through the telling of epic and highly visual stories, relevant to contemporary issues.\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 TEACHING\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Complementarily to the direction of the company, Stephen Bain and France Herv\'8e, give regular pedagogic classes in schools and theatre centres, recently including;\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Toi Whakaari\: The Drama School of New Zealand, Wellington Performing Arts Centre,  UCOL - Manawatu Polytechnique Palmerston North, Eastern Institute of Technology, Alliance Fran\'8daise de Wellington }
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 (French theatre workshops)}
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 ,  }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Acad\'8emie Internationale de la Danse }
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 (Paris 16\'8f)}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 , Cours Thierry Hamon }
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 (Bilingual theatre course - Paris 1999-2000}
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 )}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 , }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Victoria University of Wellington }
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 (Workshops and Tutoring), }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 also}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 regular professional training and workshops in Wellington and Auckland}
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 .\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Together they have defined an original technique,  \'d4motiv-e-motion\'d5 organically combining text, voice and movement, using the spoken word and the theatrical space to advance narritive.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 MOTV-E-MOTION\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Motive}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1  Implies a principle of thought that makes us act after determination. \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Motion }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 Quality of what is alive, what is not inert.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 Finally}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 , }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 e-}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  as in }
{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Energie }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 that completes the word}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  }
{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Emotion\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1  Instinctive sensibility to the source of feelings.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2Enticed by the world of symbolism, we approach theatrical creation with the intuition not dissimilar to that of a painter or cinematographer.  We want, before all else, to give to the public the chance and the pleasure to use their power of abstraction.\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
