\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 The first major play written by the celebrated French playwrite Paul Claudel, }
{\plain\b\i\f20\fs24\cf1 The Exchange }
{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 confronts the \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\i\f20\fs24\cf1 desires of love and freedom through four characters, simulataneously representing opposing aspects of the same soul. Four ideals without compromise, suffering the satisfaction of their individual interests.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 A first english adaptation of Paul Claudel\'d5s play, highly visual and imaginative,  fusing the poetry of the words to a  choreographic precision\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 The native Ameriacn references of the original script have been supplanted, allowing a New Zealand sensibility and relevance to the native maori.\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2To run away! It\'d5s not the point! To come to an end, that is a beautiful notion\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 International Theatre Season - Downstage Theatre Wellington\par }
