\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 A magical amalgam of music, dance and language, the production}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  of the Exchange by Under Lili\'d5s Balcony}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1  is theatre both thrilling and profoundly challenging}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 . The music, from Jeff Hendreson on the saxophone and Steve Cournane on drums and percussion, accompagnies the actors, moulding and supporting their words and movements. Steven Marriott Lloyd\'d5s set is stunning with its grainy walls and polished steel floor}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 , while Andrew Foester\'d5s lighting is superb. Original in concept, daring in design, immaculately performed, }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 The Exchange}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1   }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 is the most exciting production in Wellington this year.\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 The Evening Post 4 Juil  \'d497}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2The four actors use the entire space with great dexterity. The physical expression of emotions is highly charged, always appropriate, and exciting to watch. A remarkable production.\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 City Voice 10 Juil  \'d497}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2Lechy hovering above the stage in a billowing white dress, a pair of lighted hands writing a letter out of the darkness, Marthe and Louis as syncopated, puffing factory machines, Louis and Thomas sprinting again and again to the sides of the stage and fli}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 nging themselves against the wall.  The actors throw themselves into this  }
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 work with deep and impresive physical commitment. Visually - and physically - the play is a knockout.\'d3\par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\b\f20\fs24\cf1 Capital Times July 1997}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \par }
\pard\ql{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 \'d2 There is a synergy between movement, text and drama from creating their own intelligent and moving translation. An elegant seemlessness, which sees Under Lili\'d5s Balcony move beyond the loose pigeon holes of \'d4dance theatre\'d5,  to create distinctive contemp}
{\plain\f20\fs24\cf1 orary performance.\'d3 \par }
